the process started but hit a lookup failure, so some skills weren’t checked. I want to be honest about that.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating task results**\\n\\nThe task says I need to report the check results, even if they’re partial due to an abort. I’m considering trying a fallback or degradation since if a tool step fails, the protocol suggests I should retry or mark it as blocked. I should probably rerun individual checks for unprocessed skills after the failure. To provide evidence of a retry, I could use a shell loop to update each skill individually, while handling errors along the way.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating update process**\\n\\nI've run `clawhub update --all`, as the user requested. To ensure everything is covered, I should consider running individual checks to prevent a single missing skill from stopping the whole process. This makes sense since the initial command might also update skills, and there was no explicit prohibition against that. However, the goal seems to be checking for update availability rather than applying updates immediately. The command might print whether everything is up to date, which is important to clarify.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Checking skill updates**\\n\\nSince no skills were updated in the first attempt, I might run checks on the remaining ones individually to see their status. I’ll avoid using `--force`, but if there are updates available, they could be applied. This aligns with the \\\"update check\\\", though changes outside the workspace might be handled fine under the cron job. There's no need to ask first since the task authorizes it. I should inspect which skills are current and maybe use `clawhub update` for each remaining skill to get their statuses.\"}]}"},{"type":"text","text":"我补一次“分项检查”重试，避免单个缺失技能把整轮扫描直接打断。","textSignature":"{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_02cc338cb0c318620169cebd05aa98819a8a8f2481f375d75c\",\"phase\":\"commentary\"}"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_3L5nI6JCG1TATD4qlyaKLsDJ|fc_02cc338cb0c318620169cebd05ba44819ab7d582e466f893c0","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"clawhub update --help","workdir":"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace","timeout":60,"yieldMs":60000,"security":"allowlist"},"partialJson":"{\"command\":\"clawhub update --help\",\"workdir\":\"/Users/ling/.openclaw/workspace\",\"timeout\":60,\"yieldMs\":60000,\"security\":\"allowlist\"}"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"gmn","model":"gpt-5.4","usage":{"input":390,"output":1043,"cacheRead":30720,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":32153,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775156463337,"responseId":"resp_02cc338cb0c318620169cebcf0459c819a9804d91d3c7c2bfc"}}
