{"type":"message","id":"8ae5e219","parentId":"f1056db9","timestamp":"2026-04-02T19:03:22.306Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Clarifying tool updates**\n\nI need to note that the xiaohongshu-search-summarizer and xiaohongshu-skill both reported as \"updated,\" but the installed versions still show as 1.0.3 and 1.0.2, with no actual version bump visible. It’s important to mention that. Also, the local openclaw version hasn’t been updated yet. And, I might want to summarize the events concisely. The initial `clawhub update --all` was aborted due to the stock-daily-report missing from the registry, so we completed a fallback check per skill.\n\n**Categorizing updates and issues**\n\nI need to list updates by category. For actual updates, context-memory-optimizer has gone from 1.0.2 to 1.0.5. The CLI for xiaohongshu-search-summarizer reported updated to 1.0.3, but there's no visible version change from the pre-check list. Similarly, xiaohongshu-skill said it was updated to 1.0.2, with no visible change either.\n\nSome local changes were skipped, like multi-search-engine and several others. Additionally, suspicious items like todo-tracker and missing skills, such as the stock-daily-report, add complexity. I might want to clarify the reasons for the first run abort and mention the current installed list count of 18 as well.\n\n**Updating OpenClaw versions**\n\nI need to mention the OpenClaw versions: the local version is 2026.3.28 (f9b1079), while the latest available via npm is 2026.4.1. It’s clear that a newer version exists, but per my instructions, I'm not updating OpenClaw itself right now. I should include a note like \"本轮未执行 openclaw 本体更新\" to emphasize that the core OpenClaw update hasn’t been executed in this round. It's just important to keep everything clear!","thinkingSignature":"{\"id\":\"rs_02cc338cb0c318620169cebd6232e4819abc6da96b8a0696d7\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABpzr11Dka-l1XlLPw0BKa